-- United’s De Gea May Need Eye Surgery, Guardian Says: Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2012-01-20T10:26:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/united-s-de-gea-may-need-eye-surgery-guardian-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  De Gea Surgery  Manchester United  goalkeeper David de Gea may need surgery
to correct eyesight problems,  the Guardian  reported.  De Gea, who wears contact lenses, was dropped the last
three games after making several mistakes, the Guardian said.  Berbatov Stays  Dimitar Berbatov doesn’t plan to leave United, the  Daily
Mirror  reported, citing his agent Emile Danchev.  Bayern Munich and Berbatov’s former team Bayer Leverkusen
have been linked with the 30-year-old striker, the Mirror said.  Gaitan Pursuit  Manchester United and Manchester City are trailing Benfica
midfielder Nicolas Gaitan, the  Daily Mail  reported.  Gaitan has a 37.5 million-pound ($58 million) release
clause in his contract, according to the Mail.  Terrace Return  Aston Villa  may introduce a standing section for fans at
its Villa Park stadium,  the Guardian  reported.  Top-tier teams in  England  switched to all-seat arenas
following the 1989 Hillsborough disaster.  To contact the reporters on this story:
